labels.label:
Parses S3 Trigger to retrieve bucket 
and key for new telemetry file

Retrieves the new Telemetry File 
that landed in S3 bucket

Sends events to two different 
folders in S3 bucket based on
routing rule configured.

Routes, Filters and Transforms 
the events int JSON based 
on routing rules using SQL.

Mock Data for S3 Trigger to test locally 
before deploying as function.
 
After setting up S3 buckets and uploading
sample telemetry into bucket, right click
on processor and select 'Run Once'

The function that processing new telemetry data 
from an S3 bucket, does processing and sends
transformed data into different S3 folders

parameters.name: aws_access_key_password
parameters.description: AWS secret access key secret to fetch and write objects to S3

parameters.name: routing_rule_geo_event
parameters.description: The rule to filter and route for certain types of types of events

parameters.name: s3_region
parameters.description: The region where the bucket is located.

parameters.name: aws_access_key_id
parameters.description: AWS access key id to fetch and write objects to S3 bucket

parameters.name: routing_rule_speed_event
parameters.description: The rule to filter and route for certain types of types of events
parameters.value: SELECT * FROM FLOWFILE where eventSource = 'truck_speed_event' and speed > 40

parameters.name: s3_dest_path_speed_event
parameters.description: The S3 folder that certain filtered events will be written to.

parameters.name: s3_dest_path_geo_event
parameters.description: The S3 folder that certain filtered events will be written to.

parameters.name: s3_bucket
parameters.description: S3 bucket where telemetry data will be processed
